.TH WLANPI-SHELL 1 "January 2026" "WLAN Pi" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wlanpi-shell \- Opinionated shell configuration for WLAN Pi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Provides optimized vim, tmux, and bash configurations for network professionals working with WLAN Pi devices.

.SH Vim keybindings
.B Leader key:
Space

.PP
.B File operations
.RS
Space+w    Save file
.RE
.RS
Space+q    Quit
.RE
.RS
Space+h    Clear search highlighting
.RE

.PP
.B Splits
.RS
Space+v    Vertical split
.RE
.RS
Space+s    Horizontal split
.RE
.RS
Space+wh   Move to left window
.RE
.RS
Space+wj   Move to window below
.RE
.RS
Space+wk   Move to window above
.RE
.RS
Space+wl   Move to right window
.RE

.PP
.B Buffers
.RS
Space+bn   Next buffer
.RE
.RS
Space+bp   Previous buffer
.RE
.RS
Space+bd   Delete buffer
.RE

.PP
.B Tabs
.RS
Ctrl+h     Previous tab
.RE
.RS
Ctrl+l     Next tab
.RE

.SH Tmux keybindings
.B Prefix key:
Ctrl+b (default)

.PP
.B Session management
.RS
Prefix+Ctrl+s    Choose session
.RE

.PP
.B Window management
.RS
Prefix+c         Create new window
.RE
.RS
Prefix+;         Last window
.RE
.RS
Prefix+n         Next window
.RE
.RS
Prefix+p         Previous window
.RE

.PP
.B Pane management
.RS
Prefix+h/j/k/l   Navigate panes (vim-style)
.RE
.RS
Prefix+"         Split horizontal
.RE
.RS
Prefix+%         Split vertical
.RE
.RS
Prefix+z         Zoom/unzoom pane
.RE
.RS
Prefix+S         Synchronize panes
.RE

.PP
.B Resize mode
.RS
Prefix+r         Enter resize mode
.RE
.RS
h/j/k/l          Resize panes (vim-style)
.RE
.RS
Escape           Exit resize mode
.RE

.PP
.B Copy mode
.RS
Prefix+[         Enter copy mode
.RE
.RS
v                Begin selection
.RE
.RS
y                Copy selection
.RE
.RS
Prefix+p         Paste
.RE

.SH Bash aliases
.B System monitoring
.RS
journal          Follow system journal
.RE
.RS
running          List running services
.RE
.RS
failed           List failed services
.RE
.RS
temps            Show Pi temperature and voltage
.RE

.PP
.B Network tools
.RS
ports            List open ports (ss)
.RE
.RS
connections      Count established connections
.RE
.RS
listening        Show listening ports
.RE

.PP
.B File operations
.RS
ll               Detailed list
.RE
.RS
la               List all including hidden
.RE
.RS
lt               List by time
.RE
.RS
lS               List by size
.RE

.SH Customization
.B Changing default editor
.PP
To change from vim to nano, add to ~/.bashrc:
.PP
.RS
export EDITOR=nano
.RE
.RS
export VISUAL=nano
.RE

.SH FILES
/etc/skel/.vimrc
.br
/etc/skel/.tmux.conf
.br
/etc/skel/.bash_aliases
.br
/etc/skel/.bashrc.d/wlanpi-shell

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vim (1),
.BR tmux (1),
.BR bash (1)

